<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xml" href="https://4brunu.github.io/feed.xslt.xml"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><generator uri="http://jekyllrb.com" version="3.3.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://4brunu.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://4brunu.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2017-01-29T00:00:21+00:00</updated><id>https://4brunu.github.io//</id><title type="html">4brunu.github.io</title><subtitle>iOS, Android and Code</subtitle><author><name>Bruno Coelho</name></author><entry><title type="html">Hello World!</title><link href="https://4brunu.github.io/blog/2017/01/28/hello-world" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hello World!" /><published>2017-01-28T22:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2017-01-28T22:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://4brunu.github.io/blog/2017/01/28/hello-world</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://4brunu.github.io/blog/2017/01/28/hello-world">&lt;p&gt;Hi, this is my first blog post!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this blog you will find content related to my experience as software developer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Last year I had the opportunity to try and learn a lot of new things, like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Reuse the business logic in C++ on iOS and Android using &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dropbox/djinni&quot;&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;New Software architectures (&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model%E2%80%93view%E2%80%93presenter&quot;&gt;MVP&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model%E2%80%93view%E2%80%93viewmodel&quot;&gt;MVVM&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane&quot;&gt;Fastlane&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jenkins.io&quot;&gt;Jenkins&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://travis-ci.org&quot;&gt;Travis-CI&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_integration&quot;&gt;Continuous Integration&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_delivery&quot;&gt;Continuous Delivery&lt;/a&gt;
among others, which I’m planning to write here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To do the things I wrote above, I received lot’s of help from the community like &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane&quot;&gt;Fastlane&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dropbox/djinni&quot;&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt;, some slack channels like &lt;a href=&quot;ios.slack.com&quot;&gt;ios.slack.com&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;androidtalks.slack.com&quot;&gt;androidtalks.slack.com&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;mobilecpp.slack.com&quot;&gt;mobilecpp.slack.com&lt;/a&gt;, and that gave me motivation to give something back to the community.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This blog is hosted on &lt;a href=&quot;https://pages.github.com&quot;&gt;Github Pages&lt;/a&gt; and it’s built using &lt;a href=&quot;https://jekyllrb.com&quot;&gt;Jekyll&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://travis-ci.org&quot;&gt;Travis-CI&lt;/a&gt;, which I’m going to talk about on the next post.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Bruno Coelho</name></author><category term="jekyll" /><category term="github-pages" /><summary type="html">Hi, this is my first blog post!</summary></entry></feed>
